# Built retrieval artifacts (rebuilt by POST /index). Also covers
# .kb/faiss_index/ (Stack B's regenerable binary index, per issue #104).
# NOTE: .kb/index.json (Wiki/BM25) and .kb/faiss_index/ (RAG) are intentionally
# force-committed (git add -f) as the first-run/demo seed so a fresh clone can
# answer /chat immediately without re-running ingest/index. Regenerate them with
# the commands in README ("Rebuilding the indexes") before committing whenever
# docs/ or wiki/ change — and rebuild the Wiki index via POST /index (NOT an eval
# run, which clobbers .kb/index.json with a docs/-based index).
.kb/

# Phase 8 retrieval comparison (eval/paraphrase_comparison/) intermediate state.
# The committed deliverables — queries.yaml, corpus/, wiki/, report.md, and the
# FINAL charts/*.png — are tracked (force-added). These two are NOT: the
# per-paraphrase verdict dumps (churn during metric tuning) and the atomic-write
# temp files. Charts are force-committed once finalised; routine regeneration
# during iteration is otherwise ignored to avoid binary churn (PRD #100 commit
# policy, issue #104).
eval/paraphrase_comparison/results/*.json
eval/paraphrase_comparison/charts/*.tmp

# /raw/ — local-only import inbox (gitignored; use examples/raw/ for samples)
# Leading / anchors the pattern to the repo root so examples/raw/ is NOT ignored.
# Copy examples/raw/*.html or .md into raw/ to try POST /import without committing.
# raw/README.md is the exception: committed so the inbox is discoverable.
/raw/*
!/raw/README.md

# wiki/ — generated artifacts and per-user runtime traces (see wiki/README.md)
wiki/index.md
wiki/lint-report.md
wiki/log.md
wiki/hot.md

# vector_rag/ (Stack B) runtime trace — decoupled from markdown_kb's wiki/log.md
# (issue #103); same append-only Wiki Log discipline, own file.
vector_rag/log.md

# gateway/ runtime trace — per-app log channel for the Gateway composition layer
# (issue #161 Phase 11 Slice 3); same append-only discipline, own file.
gateway/log.md

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# DeepEval (Phase 8 eval framework) — machine-local telemetry + cache, regenerable.
.deepeval/
.deepeval-cache.json

# Secrets
.env
.env.local

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
.tmp/

# Personal local notes (codebase walkthrough lessons, scratch docs)
.doc.local/
